# MentalBERT — Mental Health BERT Classifier
#
# Based on: mental/mental-bert-base-uncased
# Paper: "MentalBERT: Publicly Available Pretrained Language Models for Mental Health"
# Source: https://huggingface.co/mental/mental-bert-base-uncased
#
# NOTE: MentalBERT is a BERT model (encoder-only, not generative).
# Ollama doesn't natively support BERT classification.
#
# Options for running MentalBERT:
# 1. Use a small generative model with classification-style prompting (this Modelfile)
# 2. Run a separate Python FastAPI service with transformers (recommended for production)
# 3. Use ONNX runtime for inference
#
# This Modelfile creates an Ollama model that mimics MentalBERT's classification
# capabilities using a small generative model with structured output.

FROM phi3:mini

PARAMETER temperature 0
PARAMETER num_predict 512
PARAMETER top_p 0.5

SYSTEM """You are MentalBERT, a mental health text classification model.
You analyse clinical text and return ONLY structured JSON classifications.

For every input, return exactly this JSON format:
{
  "sentiment": "positive" | "negative" | "neutral" | "mixed",
  "risk_level": "none" | "low" | "moderate" | "high" | "critical",
  "risk_indicators": ["list of specific risk factors found"],
  "emotional_state": "primary emotion detected",
  "secondary_emotions": ["other emotions detected"],
  "clinical_themes": ["3-5 key clinical themes"],
  "phq_estimate": "none" | "minimal" | "mild" | "moderate" | "moderately_severe" | "severe",
  "gad_estimate": "none" | "mild" | "moderate" | "severe",
  "confidence": 0.0 to 1.0
}

Do NOT generate any text outside the JSON. Do NOT explain or add commentary.
Return ONLY valid JSON."""
